title: For Sale:  Charter Arms Bulldog Classic 44 Special
postcontent:
This gun has a strange and sordid past.  It's the weapon carried in the Son of Sam killings, as well as being the weapon of choice for detective Jack Crawford in Thomas Harris' novel Red Dragon.

This gun was super popular in the '70's for being a large caliber revolver weighing in at a light ~22 ounces, this guns manufacture is 1974.  This gun is great for backpacking and outdoorsman as you can really pack a punch with the 44 special.  

This pistol includes Pachmayr grips, the original wooden grips, and a custom molded Kydex holster. 

Check gunbroker.com to verify that you are getting an excellent price on this revolver (the newly released "classic" model retails for ~$800).  SB 941 doesn't take effect until August 9th, so buy it before then : )  Must be legal for you to own this gun in Oregon, minimum requirement of Oregon Driver's License and bill of sale.
